						               													<description>National Liberation Front: A Game of Guerrilla Warfare in Today's World . . . [I]ntroduces new and unique design concepts that promote realistic military situations, including command problems that must deal with secret and simultaneous unit movements. Your strategy, consequently, must be based solely on the last known position of the enemy. A given enemy unit's strength is not known until contact has been established. Both, the government and the guerrillas, have different but equally difficult tasks ahead of them. Every aspect of the game has been carefully developed for easy playability but maintains a high level of combat simulation. Many original and innovative design concepts make this rare combination possible. When it is over, perhaps we, as players, will have reached a greater insight into the most prevalent type of warfare in the world today.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
